description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Respiratory Physiotherapist - COPD&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6/7 depending on experience. Band 7 Salary:£40,681 - £46,294 pa, pro rata, incl HCAS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 22.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has become available to join the integrated respiratory team to cover maternity leave. A fixed term contract until February 2022 or a secondment opportunity is available for internal staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The integrated respiratory team comprises of Respiratory Consultant, specialist nurses, specialist physiotherapist and specialist occupational therapist. The team strive to deliver a person centred holistic respiratory care across the patient pathway.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly experienced physiotherapist with previous experience of treating patients with respiratory disease including pulmonary rehab and oxygen assessments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have an active role to play within the integrated respiratory service across primary and secondary care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The integrated team is based at hospital trust providing community respiratory care for the local population as well as inpatient care and specialist outpatient clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a forward thinking and dynamic therapist looking to further your professional experience then we would like to hear from you. There may be other opportunities within the trust as we look to expand respiratory care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Car owner/Driver is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like further information regarding the post please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sarah Pearce (Respiratory Lead Nurse) - 01483 571122 ext 6866&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Jenny Steedman (Respiratory Physiotherapist) - 01483 571122 ext 4677&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 22/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview: TBC&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
